{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% set pair = card_data.pair_centerpiece %}
{% set stress = card_data.stress_scenarios[2] %}

{% macro exact_stat(stat_id, label, value, domain="overlap") -%}
{% set rail_position = value * 100 if domain == "overlap" else (value + 1) * 50 %}
<div class="interval-stat m4-exact" id="{{ stat_id }}-stat" data-domain="{{ domain }}"
     data-lo="{{ value }}" data-point="{{ value }}" data-hi="{{ value }}">
  <span class="interval-stat__label">{{ label }}</span>
  <span class="interval-stat__value" id="{{ stat_id }}-value">{% if domain == "cosine" %}{{ "%.3f"|format(value) }}{% else %}{{ "%.1f"|format(value * 100) }}%{% endif %}</span>
  <div class="interval-stat__rail">
    <div class="interval-stat__band" style="left: {{ rail_position }}%; width: 0"></div>
    <div class="interval-stat__point" style="left: {{ rail_position }}%"></div>
  </div>
  <span class="interval-stat__range">exact for this snapshot; no sampling interval</span>
</div>
{%- endmacro %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/pages/m4.css">
{% endblock %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="m4-intro">
  <p class="m4-headline">
    The labels say diversifiers. Their position holdings say otherwise: {{ pair.manager_a }} and
    {{ pair.manager_b }} share {{ "%.1f"|format(pair.raw * 100) }}% of their signed books, but
    {{ "%.1f"|format(pair.liquidity * 100) }}% of their unwind footprints because the shared
    names are harder to exit. This is a point-in-time measurement and a liquidation
    <strong>scenario, not a forecast</strong>.
  </p>
  <span class="tier-badge" data-tier="P">Position holdings &middot; exact snapshot</span>
  <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="robust">measurement only</span>
</section>

<section class="m4-panel" aria-labelledby="m4-pair-title">
  <h2 id="m4-pair-title">The two-manager unwind panel</h2>
  <p id="m4-selected-pair" class="m4-selected">{{ pair.manager_a }} &times; {{ pair.manager_b }}</p>
  <div class="m4-stats">
    {{ exact_stat("m4-raw", "Raw directional overlap", pair.raw) }}
    {{ exact_stat("m4-liquidity", "Liquidity-adjusted overlap", pair.liquidity) }}
    {{ exact_stat("m4-cosine", "Signed holdings-vector cosine", pair.cosine, "cosine") }}
  </div>
  <p class="m4-note">
    The first two values are fractions of book and unwind time. The cosine is an angle between
    signed holdings vectors, not a return-correlation estimate.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="m4-panel" aria-labelledby="m4-heatmap-title">
  <h2 id="m4-heatmap-title">Roster liquidity-overlap heat map</h2>
  <p class="m4-note">Select any off-diagonal cell to inspect its three precomputed measurements.</p>
  <div class="m4-heatmap" role="grid" aria-label="Pairwise liquidity-adjusted overlap">
    {% for row_name in card_data.heatmap.managers %}
      {% set i = loop.index0 %}
      {% for col_name in card_data.heatmap.managers %}
        {% set j = loop.index0 %}
        {% set value = card_data.heatmap.liquidity[i][j] %}
        <button type="button" class="m4-cell{% if i == j %} m4-cell--self{% endif %}"
                role="gridcell" data-i="{{ i }}" data-j="{{ j }}"
                aria-label="{{ row_name }} and {{ col_name }}, liquidity-adjusted overlap {{ '%.1f'|format(value * 100) }} percent"
                style="--heat: {{ value }}" {% if i == j %}disabled{% endif %}>
          {{ "%.0f"|format(value * 100) }}%
        </button>
      {% endfor %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<aside class="m4-guide" aria-label="What this exhibit shows">
  <h2>What this exhibit shows</h2>
  <div>
    <h3>What you are looking at</h3>
    <p>
      A six-manager synthetic roster on one shared market. The heat map measures the common
      unwind footprint of every pair; the centrepiece opens the hottest unexpected pair and
      shows the same-direction positions they would both need to exit.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>How to read it</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Raw overlap is the common signed weight; opposite directions are offsets.</li>
      <li>Liquidity overlap re-expresses each book in days-to-cover shares.</li>
      <li>The slider selects a precomputed stressed-volume scenario; it does not predict loss.</li>
      <li>The dashed impact annotation is illustrative and is not part of the exact bars.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The formulas, evidence requirements, and validation tests are in the
      <a href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}specs/{{ card.id }}.html">technical method and provenance</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</aside>

<section class="m4-panel" aria-labelledby="m4-stress-title">
  <h2 id="m4-stress-title">Common-holder unwind scenario</h2>
  <div class="m4-slider">
    <label for="m4-stress-delta">Stressed volume available</label>
    <input id="m4-stress-delta" class="m4-slider__range"
           type="range" min="0" max="4" step="1" value="2">
    <output id="m4-stress-output" for="m4-stress-delta">50%</output>
  </div>
  <p class="m4-note">
    At the selected 50% volume state, {{ pair.worst_asset }} ({{ pair.worst_direction }}) is
    {{ "%.1f"|format(pair.worst_days_stressed_volume) }} days of stressed volume. Exact bars
    measure the footprint under the chosen input; they do not predict a liquidation.
  </p>
  <div id="m4-unwind-bars" class="m4-bars" aria-live="polite">
    {% for row in stress.rows %}
    <div class="m4-bar" data-row="{{ loop.index0 }}">
      <div class="m4-bar__label">
        <span>{{ row.asset }} &middot; {{ row.direction }}</span>
        <strong class="m4-bar__value">{{ "%.1f"|format(row.days_stressed_volume) }} days</strong>
      </div>
      <div class="m4-bar__track"><span style="width: {{ row.days_stressed_volume / stress.worst.days_stressed_volume * 100 }}%"></span></div>
      <div class="m4-impact">illustrative impact {{ "%.2f"|format(row.illustrative.impact_rate * 100) }}% &mdash; illustrative &mdash; not a forecast</div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="m4-panel" aria-labelledby="m4-tier-title">
  <h2 id="m4-tier-title">Evidence limits are part of the result</h2>
  <div class="m4-tier"><span class="tier-badge" data-tier="P">Position holdings</span><p>Name-level overlap and unwind measurement can render.</p></div>
  <div class="m4-tier"><span class="tier-badge" data-tier="E">Exposure summaries</span><p>Factor crowding only; no name-level overlap and no unwind stress.</p></div>
  <div class="m4-tier"><span class="tier-badge" data-tier="R">Returns only</span><p>Descriptive return co-movement only &mdash; not a holdings measurement, no unwind scenario, no size cap.</p></div>
  <div class="power-gate">
    <span class="power-gate__title">Public-filings view unavailable</span>
    <p class="power-gate__reason">
      Form 13F is a US regulatory filing that reports certain long equity positions. No
      public-filings panel renders until validation quantifies its 45-day lag, longs-only
      coverage, coverage gaps in the filing universe, and non-US blindness.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="m4-panel" aria-labelledby="m4-gate-title">
  <h2 id="m4-gate-title">Predictive claim refused</h2>
  <div class="power-gate">
    <span class="power-gate__title">Scenario, not forecast &middot; predictive validation unavailable</span>
    <p class="power-gate__reason">
      Overlap and stressed-volume measurements render. No predicted loss or size-cap
      recommendation renders before the overlap-decile versus co-drawdown operating
      characteristic exists. If predictive validation fails, the measurement stays while exit-risk and
      size-cap framing are removed.
    </p>
  </div>
  <p class="m4-note">
    This exhibit measures crowding; it does not allocate. A separate allocation method may
    consume a validated measurement as a constraint later, but this exhibit never computes
    portfolio weights.
  </p>
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>
  Raw overlap is directional common weight: the smaller absolute position counts only where
  both managers hold the name in the same direction. Liquidity overlap applies the same
  measure after each book is normalized in days-to-cover space. The unwind report then sums
  same-direction dollar holders and divides by stressed dollar volume. These are exact
  snapshot measurements with position holdings; the loss interpretation remains unvalidated.
</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block body_scripts %}
<script src="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/m4-crowding.js"></script>
{% endblock %}
